FBIS3-8450 "dreeu047_d_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 SLOVAKIA HZDS Parliament Group Deputy Chairman Resigns LD0903201594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1600 GMT 9 Mar 94 LD0903201594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network in Slovak 1600 GMT 9 Mar 94 Language: Slovak Article Type:BFN [Text] Imrich Mori, deputy chairman of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia parliamentary group, has confirmed to the press agency [as heard] that he resigned from his post at yesterday's session of the parliamentary group. The reason for the decision is his fundamental disagreement with the formulation of the second question of the referendum, which concerns the withdrawal of deputies' mandate.
